**Model fit**

Bentler-Bonett non-normed fit index (NNFI), Bollen (IFI) fit index, comparative fit index (CFI), and root-mean-square error of approximation (RMSEA) were used to evaluate the model fit. NNFI, IFI, and CFI are incremental fit indices whose values range from 0 to 1. Their value above 0.90 or 0.95 are indications of well fit [[59](#59 "59"),[60](#60 "60")]. However, CFI has been suggested as the index of choice [[61](#61 "61")]. RMSEA is the misfit measure whose value can range from 0 to 1, so the smaller the value, the better fit. However, the value<0.05 is considered good fit [[62](#62 "62")]. Chambok’s model (**Figure 2**) had NNFI=0.963, CFI=0.965, IFI=0.972, and RMSEA=0.007, the confidence interval of RMSEA=(0.00, 0.02). Thus, Chambok’s model was well fit. Chi Phat’s model (**Figure 3**) have NNFI=0.880, CFI=0.900, IFI=0.904, and RMSEA=0.049 the confidence interval of RMSEA= (0.039, 0.050). Although NNFI is a bit lower than 0.90, this model can also be considered acceptable fit model.

